<item>
            <title>[CXF-5116] DelegatingInputStream created in AbstractHTTPDestination is cached into wrong Message instance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5116</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DelegatingInputStream instance created in AbstractHTTPDestination uses the passed Message instance to cache HttpServletRequest inputs. However in ChainInitiationObserver::onMessage a new SoapMessage is created by copying the existing request message contents, so when the DelegatingInputStream caching is triggered, the input data is saved in wrong message instance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The result is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2911&quot; title=&quot;HttpServletRequest.getScheme()  returns null in one way webservice method&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-2911&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-2911&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; bug is still valid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
